  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth Version: 1.5.7-stable\r\nGit Commit: da2a22c384a9b621ec853fe4b1aa651d606cf42b\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.7.4\r\nOS: darwin\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=/usr/local/Cellar/go/1.7.4_2/libexec\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nExecute the following on the Geth cli:  \r\n```\r\nconst account = '0xfa3da03af4709506b56b26e409d1cdacf9d16fc5';\r\nlet sha3Msg = web3.sha3(\"abc\");\r\nlet gethMsg = web3.sha3(\"\\x19Ethereum Signed Message:\\n\" + sha3Msg.length + sha3Msg);\r\nlet signature = web3.eth.sign(account, sha3Msg);\r\nlet r, v, s;\r\n\r\nr = signature.slice(0, 66);\r\ns = '0x' + signature.slice(66, 130);\r\nv = '0x' + signature.slice(130, 132);\r\nv = web3.toDecimal(v);\r\nif (v != 27 && v != 28) v += 27;\r\n```\r\nExpect:  \r\n```\r\naccount == auth.verify.call(gethMsg, v, r, s)\r\n```\r\nthe gethMsg is right?\r\n```\r\ngethMsg \r\nlet sha3Msg = web3.sha3(\"abc\");\r\nlet gethMsg = web3.sha3(\"\\x19Ethereum Signed Message:\\n\" + sha3Msg.length + sha3Msg);\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhere \"address\" is an instance of the contract:\r\n```\r\ncontract Auth{\r\n  function test(bytes32 hash, uint8 v, bytes32 r, bytes32 s) constant returns (address) {\r\n      return ecrecover(hash, v, r, s);\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nString returned by verify does NOT match the account which was used for signing the hash\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nSee above\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\nNone, no exception\r\n````\r\n",
