    "body": "You can find an example how to retrieve the address from solidity [here](https://gist.github.com/bas-vk/d46d83da2b2b4721efb0907aecdb7ebd). \r\n\r\nIf you are using geth cli and want to check signatures created with `eth_sign` you can also use `personal.ecRecover`. It accepts the original message and the signature and returns the address. It handles the message prefixing internally. In your example: `personal.ecRecover(sha3Msg, signature)` should give you the address. No need for a solidity contract.",
